premise_source_doc_sentence: Low-alcohol beer  (  also called light beer , non-alcoholic beer , small beer , small ale , or near-beer  )  is beer with low alcohol content or no alcohol , which aims to reproduce the taste of beer without the inebriating effects of standard alcoholic brews .
Because of its very low alcohol content , non-alcoholic beer may be legally sold to minors in many American states .
Commercially produced banana wine is a clear , slightly sparkling alcoholic beverage with a longer shelf-life than banana beer , which is spoiled easily and therefore not stored for long periods .
In the United States , beverages containing less than 0.5 % alcohol by volume  (  ABV  )  were legally called non-alcoholic , according to the now-defunct Volstead Act .
Banana beer is an alcoholic beverage made from fermentation of mashed bananas .
